cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "TPMN-PSL: Truth-Provenance Markup Notation — Platform Specification Language"
version: "0.1.5-p"
date-released: "2026-03-16"
license: CC-BY-4.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/gem-squared/tpmn-psl"
url: "https://tpmn-psl.gemsquared.ai"
abstract: >
  TPMN-PSL is a platform-agnostic formal epistemic specification language
  for structuring, validating, and auditing AI reasoning. It defines a
  four-layer notation grammar (TLA+, Panini, Math, NL), a five-tag epistemic
  taxonomy (⊢ ⊨ ⊬ ⊥ ?), a three-phase checking protocol (P / Inline / O),
  and a Structural Prohibition Taxonomy (SPT) for forbidden inference patterns.
  Its primary contribution is the Panini ontological discretization layer —
  a formal mechanism for transforming NL prompts into computable, provable,
  traceable MANDATEs before LLM inference begins.
keywords:
  - epistemic markup
  - AI reasoning
  - formal specification
  - hallucination prevention
  - LLM verification
  - ontological discretization
  - truth provenance
  - specification language
